Interface Context

Object that get's passed around to provide in various iterations E.g. gives access to current crawled cinema or the date it currently iterates thouhg.

Optional auditorium

auditorium: string

The title of the auditorium showtimes are shown in

Optional callstack

callstack: string[]

Stack trace of internal methods. Provides additional context for implementing hooks or mappers.

Optional cinema

cinema: Partial<Cinema>

The cinema showtimes are crawled for, either from static config or retrieved via cinema list crawling

currentTask

currentTask: string

The currently worked on task. Use for internal progress tracking. May only be used as additinoal context hooks if requestUrl or resource is not precise enough.

Optional date

date: Moment

The date of the showtimes (without time). Retrieved either from iterating date boxes or the date of the url request.

Optional dateHref

dateHref: string

The date page's href, relative link or absolute url in case of cinemas publishing showtimes on dynamicly crawled date pages

indexes

indexes: { page?: number; tab?: number; table?: CellReference }

Current indexes of iterations

Type declaration

  • Optional page?: number

    On pagination, the index of the current page

  • Optional tab?: number

    When parsing tabs, the index of the current tab or card

  • Optional table?: CellReference

    Reference of the current table cell

isTemporarilyClosed

isTemporarilyClosed: boolean

Flag that indicates if a cinema is temporarirly clsoed.

Optional movie

movie: Partial<Movie>

The movie a showtime is for.

Optional page

page: string

on static pagination: the current pages value

Optional parentContext

parentContext: Context

The context which this context is cloned from. Was the framework is traversing through deep nested html structures and multiple urls, the context is cloned to allow adding details to it that is not relevant in broader scopes.
